definitions.definition: Items thrown overboard from a ship or boat in distress in order to lighten its load .
examples: There she was, floating amongst the jetsam , like so much debris.

definitions.definition: Discarded or leftover odds and ends .
examples: They were the jetsam of the dot-com bust.

main_definition: Items thrown overboard from a ship or boat in distress in order to lighten its load .
secondary_definitions: ( by extension ) Discarded or leftover odds and ends .
